Lucide Icons
============

Source:  https://lucide.dev
Repo:    https://github.com/lucide-icons/lucide
License: ISC (see LICENSE)

The SVG files in this directory are vendored from the upstream Lucide
project at the commit referenced by the project's documentation.
Lucide was originally forked from Feather (MIT, Cole Bemis 2013-2022)
and has since been substantially extended by the Lucide Contributors
(2022-present).

Per UI Design Book §3.6 (Iconography), Lucide is the single icon family
used throughout the DAW UI:

  - monochrome line icons
  - 16 px nominal (also 20 / 24 for sidebar density)
  - 1.5 px optical stroke (rendered from Lucide's native 2 px @ 24 viewBox)
  - inherits CSS `-fx-icon-color` so the same icon flips with the theme

Adding a new Lucide icon
------------------------

1. Download the SVG from https://lucide.dev/icons/ into this directory.
2. Add the icon's base name (without `.svg`) to `icons.allowed.txt`.
3. The `LucideIconInventoryTest` will fail until those two sets match —
   this is intentional: it prevents drift toward "every developer adds
   one more icon" (UI Design Book §3.6).

Removing an icon
----------------

1. Delete the `.svg` file.
2. Remove the name from `icons.allowed.txt`.
3. Verify no UI code still references the icon name via `DawgIcon.of(...)`.
